@subsection Executing Lazily


The @pxref{7,,exec} function returns result sets as eager lists which can
sometimes be inefficient or simply not feasible for large result
sets. In such cases it is preferable to use @pxref{1a,,lexec} instead of
@pxref{7,,exec}.

@geindex sql3;;lexec (function)
@anchor{pure-sql3 sql3 lexec}@anchor{1a}
@deffn {Pure Function} sql3::lexec stmp::stmt_ptr args

same as @pxref{7,,exec} except that it returns a lazy list.
@end deffn

Example:

@example
> lexec sp2 19;
["Sam",20]:#<thunk 0xb6475ab0>
@end example

@noindent

Note that no changes to @code{sp2} were required. In addition, for most
purposes the lazy list returned by @pxref{1a,,lexec} can be processed by the
same code that processed the eager list returned by @pxref{7,,exec}.

@node Executing Directly on a db_ptr,Executing Against a Busy Database,Executing Lazily,Prepared Statements
